*$
* EL6256 Macromodel
* Revision A, February 1997
* Application Hints:
* This macromodel contains every pin needed for the device and will model
* the behavoir of these pins with the exception that it will not model the
* oscillator.
*  For best results, users need to accurately model the amount of inductance
* in series  with the laserdiode, as well as the laserdiode characteristics (L, * C, R etc). Damping  networks to idealize their waveforms may be added.
* Users must connect to the following pins at MINIMUM  !!: 
* VCC, IOUT, OUTENR, and IINR
* All other pins may be left floating if not used
*  
.subckt EL6256/EL  IINR IN2 RFREQ IIN3 IIN4 OUTENR OUTEN2 OUTEN3 OUTEN4 VCC
+OSCEN ENABLE  RAMP  IOUT 
.MODEL MS1 VSWITCH VON=  0  VOFF=10mV RON=100  ROFF=10MEG  
.MODEL MS2 VSWITCH VON=-0.8 VOFF=-2.4 RON=10m  ROFF=10MEG  
.MODEL MS3 VSWITCH VON= 1.7 VOFF=1.6  RON=100  ROFF=10MEG  
.MODEL MS4 VSWITCH VON=-1.6 VOFF=-1.7 RON=10m  ROFF=10MEG  
