* EL6257 Macromodel
* Revision A, May, 1997
* Application Hints:
*This macromodel contains every pin needed for the device, and will model 
*the behavior of every pin with the exception that it will not model the 
*oscillator. For best results, users need to accurately model their PC board. 
*In particular, the path to the laser diode and the laser diode characteristics 
*(L, C, R etc) need to be modelled. Many users may require damping networks on 

*the IOUT pin to achieve their preferred pulse waveform profiles.
*
*USERS MUST CONNECT TO THE FOLLOWING PINS AT A MINIMUM !:
*VCC, IOUT, OUTENR, IINR
*All other pins may be left floating if not used. 
.subckt el6257/el IINR IIN2 RFREQ IIN3 IIN4 OUTENR OUTEN2 OUTEN3 OUTEN4 VCC 
+OSCEN ENABLE RAMP IOUT
.MODEL MS1 VSWITCH VON=0    VOFF=10mV RON=100  ROFF=10MEG  
.MODEL MS2 VSWITCH VON=-0.8 VOFF=-2.4 RON=0.01 ROFF=10MEG  
.MODEL MS3 VSWITCH VON=+1.7 VOFF=+1.6 RON=100  ROFF=10MEG  
.MODEL MS4 VSWITCH VON=-1.6 VOFF=-1.7 RON=0.01 ROFF=10MEG  
C1 N2 0 100pF
C10 N12 VCC 50pF
C2  N13   0  7pF
C3  N16   0  7pF
C4  N11 VCC  8pF
C5  N5    0 3.6nF
C6  N9    0  7pF
C7  N6    0 3.6nF
C8  N8    0 3.6nF
C9  N10   0 3.6nF
FI21 VCC N4 VFI21 1
FI22 0   N9 VFI22 95
FI23 0  N20 VFI23 95
FI24 0  N13 VFI24 94
FI25 0  N16 VFI25 95
HI26 N19 N18 VHI26 775
L4 N11 IOUT 4n
R1 N5 IIN4 200 
R10 VCC OSCEN 30K 
R11 N1 N8 1 
R12 N14 N10 1 
R13 N3 N2 6 
R14 VCC ENABLE 400K 
R15 VCC OUTENR 100K 
R16 VCC OUTEN4 30K 
R17 VCC OUTEN3 30K 
R18 VCC OUTEN2 30K 
R2 N8  IIN2 200 
R3 N6  IIN3 200 
R4 N10 IINR 200 
R5 N11 N12 6    
